This paper proposes a new framework for point-data embeddings that can be used for point-set registration problems. The paper focuses on improving the speed of the embedding process and provides significant speedup for Jacobian computation. Given the focus on computer vision and machine learning techniques, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and robotics, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves geometric reasoning, which could fall under cs.GR (Computational Geometry).
